lliad” 18.452, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἕταρον γὰρ.. πέμπ᾽ Ἄϊδόσδε <b>was conducting</b> or <b>convoying</b> Patroclus to Hades, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 23.137. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> followed by <i>infinitive</i> of purpose, τὴν.. ἅρμασι π. νέεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.8; ἕπεσθαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.575; ἰέναι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.396; ἱκανέμεν 4.29; ἄγειν 24.419; φέρειν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.454 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; φέρεσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 681; μήτηρ με πέμπει πατρὶ τυμβεῦσαι χοάς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 406 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>send word</b>, πέμπεις.. σῇ δάμαρτι, παῖδα σὴν δεῦρ᾽ ἀποστέλλειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 360 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πέμπουσιν οἱ ἔφοροι.. στρατεύεσθαι <b>sent him orders</b> to march, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.1.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also with <i>participle</i>, κήρυκας π. ἀγγέλλοντας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.76.22: the place from which is expressed by ἀπό or ἐκ, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.447, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.635, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, ἐπέμψαμεν πρὸς ὑμᾶς περὶ ἀποστάσεως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.13; πέμπει κελεύων 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.91, 2.81; ἐκέλευε.. πέμπων 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.3.1; ἔπεμπε πρὸς Κῦρον δεόμενος [prev. author] “Cyr.” 1.5.4; ἔπεμπον ἐρωτῶντες [prev. author] “An.” 6.6.4, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>send forward, nominate</b> a person for a post, ὀνόματα Wilcken [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Chr.” 28.20 (2nd c.AD):\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\", [prev. work]392.7 (2nd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>send forth</b> or <b>away, dismiss, send home</b>, τὸν ξεῖνον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.227, +others: less frequently in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”, as 24.780 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χρὴ ξεῖνον παρεόντα φιλεῖν, ἐθέλοντα δὲ πέμπειν 'welcome the coming, <b>speed</b> the parting guest', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.74; ὑπέδεκτο καὶ πέμπε 23.315 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the father who sends off his daughter to go to her husband, with <i>dative</i>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.5; π. τινὰ ἄποικον 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1518, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of missiles, <b>discharge, shoot</b>, πέτρας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 716: _metaphorically_, ὄμματος.. τόξευμα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 1005: _absolutely_, οἱ πολλάκις πέμποντες ἔστιν ὅτε τυγχάνουσι τοῦ σκοποῦ 4th-5th c.AD: Eunapius Historicus “Vitae Sophistarum” p.495 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of words, <b>send forth, utter</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 443, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 846 (Lyric poetry), 1445 (_anapaest meter_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>conduct, escort</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.390, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.336, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 571, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; frequently of Hermes and other gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" ti