+</a>]; π. δῶρα, σκῦλα, ξένια, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.106 (_active_ and _passive_), 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1429, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.1.42. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>send up, produce</b>, ὅσα πέμπει βιόδωρος αἶα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1162 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> <i>middle</i>, πέμπεσθαί τινα <b>send for</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 602 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], ubiv. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Scholia; τί χρῆμ᾽ ἐπέμψω τὸν ἐμὸν ἐκ δόμων πόδ; 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 977. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> <b>send in one's own service</b> or <b>cause to be sent</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 556, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Tox.” 14. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3992","accentedUnicode":"πέμπω","shortDef":"to send","mediumDef":"<b>to send, to despatch on any message, embassy, business,</b> etc., <ref='Mat.2.8; 11:2; 14:10'>Mt. 2:8; 11:2; 14:10</ref>; <b>to transmit,</b> <ref='Act.11.29'>Acts 11:29;</ref> <ref='Rev.1.11'>Rev. 1:11;</ref> <b>to dismiss, permit to go,</b> <ref='Mrk.5.12'>Mk. 5:12</ref>; <b>to send in</b> or <b>among,</b> <ref='2Th.2.11'>2Thess. 2:11;</ref> <b>to thrust in,</b> or <b>put forth,</b> <ref='Rev.14.15, 18'>Rev. 14:15, 18</ref>","stepGloss":"to send","stepTransliteration":"pempō","count":79,"_es_Definition":"enviar ; encargar, nombrar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 打發 (某人)<br>2) (將東西) 送往","_zh_Definition":"1) 打发 (某人)<br>2) (将东西) 送往","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"gửi; sai; sai đi; sai đến.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"打發, 差","_es_Gloss":"enviar","_zh_Gloss":"打发, 差"}]}